Fun sequence from my third match at @adcc_official trials. This kid is only 20 years old & tapped 2 black belts to make it to the round of 64. He gave me a lot of trouble early in the match with his attacks from guard. Had to resort to the basics to get the job done. 

Thank you, coach @mrj_cgq, for the excellent corner as always.
3-0 on the night! That’s how we do it @faa_ct 💪🏽✅

Fun match from @adcc_official trials last week. He had just beaten the #10 seed & submitted 3 black belts on his way to the round of 32, so he was coming in with a good amount of momentum. We actually trained together a few times in preparation, but when someone is standing in your way, you have to do what you have to do.

Before you judge him for looking like he wants to fight me, just know that I was shoving my little arm into his neck so it was warranted. ALSO, before you judge me for jamming my little arm into his neck, know that he was clubbing the ever loving shit out of my head so it was justified.

We are still friends & will continue to train together. He is still very young in this game, I tried my absolute best to get the submission, but he was all heart. I am excited to see where his grappling career goes.

West Coast Trials?

Appreciate the s/o @flograppling. 

Maybe I get on a WNO show in the future? 

Also, I gave up getting submitted, so no more of that.

The points first route had proven difficult, so when I saw the sub opportunity, I jumped on it. The principles I follow for applying chokes make hooks unnecessary to finish & the merkle prevents motion to escape.

For years, Nick Newell has remained an absolute threat whether it be in the cage or on the mats. From high school and collegiate wrestling to professional MMA to jiu-jitsu tournaments, Nick has been an undeniable competitor for quite awhile. 

From fighting Justin Gaethje early in his MMA career, making history with Bellator MMA, putting fourth amazing performances at the 2023 ADCC East Coast Trials, to coaching a special crop of young fighters, you may never know the next move for “Notorious” Nick Newell. However, rest assured he isn’t going anywhere and he remains a powerhouse to the sport as a competitor and as a coach. I had the chance to catch up with Nick a few weeks ago and we talked about topics including:

✅ Reviewing Team FAA’s victories at CES
✅ Being a coach that actively competes
✅ FAA culture and relocation
✅ Nicks’s big banner from Bellator 225
✅ Current biggest prospects at FAA
✅ Message to the people who idolize Nick
✅ Pete Bencivenga’s influence 
✅ “Notorious” Nick’s Legacy
